CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) — West Virginia’s Yeager Airport is in line to receive $2.1 million from the Federal Aviation Administration, the airport said.The funds are from the Airport Infrastructure Grant program under the bipartisan infrastructure plan. More than 3,000 U.S. airports will receive funds from three new aviation programs.The funds are the first round for the Charleston airport over five years. The money could be invested in runways, taxiways, safety and sustainability projects, as well as terminal, airport-transit and roadway projects, the airport said.“We now have the opportunity to fund projects that will meet our needs for the next 30 to 40 years,” airport Director and CEO Nick Keller said.